WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.120 --> 00:00:03.729
Anchor Leadin: Although Courtney Boyll (pronounced
"boil") is paralyzed from the waist down you

00:00:03.729 --> 00:00:07.089
would never know from her joyful attitude.

00:00:07.089 --> 00:00:14.290
She lives her life with no regrets--she married
her college sweetheart and is raising three

00:00:14.290 --> 00:00:15.519
kids of her own.

00:00:15.519 --> 00:00:18.630
Despite her daily struggles to take care of
her family--and herself--she's inspiring her

00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:22.160
community one smile at a time.

00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:23.390
TAKE PKG:

00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:30.070
COURTNEY: I believe that what happened to
me was just an accident you know driving too

00:00:30.070 --> 00:00:32.660
fast down a little country road.

00:00:32.660 --> 00:00:37.289
VO: 20-years ago, Courtney Boyll was finishing
her sophomore year of high school.

00:00:37.289 --> 00:00:42.370
A standout basketball player with division-1
interests from schools all over when a car

00:00:42.370 --> 00:00:43.880
accident changed everything.

00:00:43.880 --> 00:00:47.629
COURTNEY: i was just named 1st team all state
while i was in the hospital...

00:00:47.629 --> 00:00:49.920
And i remember the doctor walking in and i
remember

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:57.829
asking him, "will i ever walk again?" and
he just flat out said, "no, i dont believe

00:00:57.829 --> 00:00:58.829
you will ever walk again."

00:00:58.829 --> 00:01:00.469
SISTER: from the moment it happened from the
first time I saw her and we had our first

00:01:00.469 --> 00:01:04.930
words since it happened it was a smile.

00:01:04.930 --> 00:01:07.660
and I was smiling and she said it's going
to be okay.

00:01:07.660 --> 00:01:12.810
COURTNEY accidents happen it's how we respond
to them that's the outcome.

00:01:12.810 --> 00:01:16.940
VO: Courtney credits her high school coaches
for teaching her just that.

00:01:16.940 --> 00:01:24.770
COURTNEY: through athletics pushed me to dig
deeper to know that it was in me to overcome

00:01:24.770 --> 00:01:27.800
to know it was in me to win.

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:34.290
And not to look at the accident as a loss,
but to overcome it and win.

00:01:34.290 --> 00:01:35.290
VO: And she has.

00:01:35.290 --> 00:01:38.210
**Nat sound teaching in the classroom to students

00:01:38.210 --> 00:01:44.060
CAMERON: when she tells me not to give up
inside of me I feel, 'don't give up.

00:01:44.060 --> 00:01:45.060
just do what ms.

00:01:45.060 --> 00:01:48.620
Courtney asks you and it will be a better
day for you tomorrow.'

00:01:48.620 --> 00:01:54.130
VO: Ms. Courtney now teaches a class of 3rd
graders and embraces the opportunity to share

00:01:54.130 --> 00:01:55.130
her story

00:01:55.130 --> 00:02:00.860
COURTNEY: you think about how many people
can say they had a teacher in a wheelchair.

00:02:00.860 --> 00:02:03.300
I know I never did.

